A health department official performs a swab test during a door-to-door COVID-19 testing drive. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is now at 4,793 with a death toll of 90. Minister of Health Zwelini Mkhize says the total number of tests conducted in the country to date is 178,470. Worldwide, the COVID-19 infection rate has passed the 3-million mark. The USA has the highest number of infections. Just under a million people have contracted the virus. Over 208,000 people have died around the globe. Health Media Release 27.04.... by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.